…..is somehow oddly satisfying. Seasoned with The Gospel AP. Smoked on the @traegergrills at 250° with hickory. Wrapped around 175° internal when the bark was perfect looking. Topped with brown sugar, Honey Hog Hot & butter in the wrap. Pulled when it was probe tender. 

#MeatChurch #TexasBBQ #PulledPork #TheGospel #Gospel

Road Trip. 

@traciepittman & I are headed to the Hill Country to cook a little BBQ for some friends. We of course had to stop at @bucees (Temple) to see how our seasonings are looking and have a chopped brisket sandwich (don’t sleep on it) + banana pudding. I had to stop traffic to take the most Texas photo ever of the @mill.scale. Ain’t mad at it.

You can keep up with our adventure in our stories. Y’all have a great weekend!

Smo-Fried Wings that just may the crispiest wings I’ve ever had!

We pulled out all the tricks to make the ultimate crispy chicken wings; cornstarch, air dry, grilling them hot on a @traegergrills + deep frying. We made these 2 ways but the wings pictured were tossed in @trybachans Hot & Spicy Japanese Barbecue Sauce and were the winner. My goodness they are probably my favorite chicken wing of all time!

Click the link in our bio to watch the video on this cook - Part 4 of our Summer Grilling Series that we shot on Cedar Creek Lake. Or grab the recipe from meatchurch.com!

node.text:
Loving my @montanaknifecompany Blackfoot 2.0! 

I had the pleasure of meeting legendary knife maker @joshsmithknives, owner of @montanaknifecompany at the @rmef_official Mountain Fest. Josh gifted me this knife which is 100% bad ass. My Papaw always bought and traded knives as a hobby when I was a kid so this brought back great memories. If your into the outdoors I would definitely give @montanaknifecompany a follow. They have amazing knives and cool stuff in the works!

#MeatChurch

Texas Twinkies. 

Huge jalapeños loaded with cream cheese & brisket. Wrapped in 2 slices of bacon. Smoked at 250° with post oak until they bacon looked perfect. D*mn these are a full meal & pure Texas BBQ!

Shout out to my dude Tim Hutchins of @hutchins_bbq for the assist since they made em famous.

Video coming soon!
